title: Dream goes on
Trivia: Before the version 2.5.2, Dream goes on and Vivid color are the only two songs with the lowest possible difficulty for a Master chart by level 10. Currently, it is the only song with the lowest Master chart difficulty of level 10 (level 9 before version 2.8 chart update).
The lyrics are in Chinese, but some parts in the chorus are in English, which makes it the first song in the game to be sung in two or more languages.
It is also the only song where two items will be given after clearing for the first time.
This song is also available in the music game Arcaea as part of its collaboration with Lanota.

title: Only the place where truth has engraved
Chronosis song
Trivia: Chronosis song and Journey are (as of 3.0) the only non-Boss Songs with cutscenes.
This song was added to Lyrica in the Lanota x Lyrica Collaboration.

title: vivid color
Trivia: Before the version 2.5.2, Dream goes on and Vivid color are the only two songs with the lowest possible difficulty for a Master chart by level 10. Currently, the Legacy chart of Dream goes on is now the only lowest Master chart difficulty at level 9.
Vivid color's Ultra chart has the lowest note count of any Ultra 8 chart, and the 2nd lowest note count of any Ultra chart, behind Umbrella.
Vivid color's Master chart has the lowest note count of any Master 11 chart, and the 2nd lowest note count of any Master chart, behind Nyever gonna Meow you Nyup.
This song has the second-lowest average note count at 307.75 across all difficulties, only larger than Umbrella.
A full version of this song appears on naoto's album "nostalgic". The song is also featured on their Spotify.

title: Ne m'oubliez pas
Trivia: The title of this song is French, meaning "Don't forget me".
*Coincidentally, the flowers in the artwork are known as forget-me-nots.
Although not credited in-game, this song was also composed by KillerBlood.

title: ciel nocturne
Trivia: The meaning of this song title in English is "nocturnal sky".
This is the first song where the Master chart was not originally the Ultra chart in 1.0.
Before the 1.5 update, this song played on the title screen.

title: DARSANA
Trivia: Every difficulty’s notecount is considered a holy number in Japanese culture (except it’s Ultra chart, which is considered an evil number), referencing the song’s title, DARSANA, which is the auspicious sight of a deity or a holy person.
This song's Acoustic chart has no green Flick notes.
This song was added to OverRapid in their respective collaboration.

title: Frey's Philosophy
Trivia: There is a fan theory about a possible character that this song is based on named Frey.
This was the only Boss Song in version 1.0, so it is also the first Boss Song in the game.
It is also the only Boss Song that gives an item after clearing for the first time.

This song can also be found in rhythm games Groove Coaster, OverRapid, [https://rotaeno.fandom.com/wiki/Frey%27s_Philosophy Rotaeno], and [https://paradigmreboot.fandom.com/wiki/Frey%27s_Philosophy Paradigm: Reboot] in their respective collaborations with Lanota.
Frey's Philosophy, Cyanine, You are the Miserable, Protoflicker's Master chart and SolarOrbit's Ultra chart share the same note count, 1444.

title: Bokura no michi
Trivia: The song title, 僕らの道 (Bokura no michi) means "Our road" in English.
The Whisper and Acoustic charts have no green Flick notes.
The Ultra chart has the lowest note count of any level 9 chart.

title: Matane
Trivia: Although not mentioned, the composer of this song's instrumental is 3R2

title: Reclaim
Trivia: This is one of only four songs where the Ultra and Master charts are the same level; the others are Bubbles Dream, Gypsophila, and Melo Melo Melon bread.
The Master chart is the Ultra chart flipped horizontally, so their note counts are the same.
The other 2 charts that has their Ultra chart has the same amount of notes compared to Master chart are 3rd Avenue, May and December and Journey.

title: cyanine
Trivia: The After 3 Challenges" artwork features the word "Apocalypse" written in The Lanota Alphabet on the device. It is heavily implied that the song Apocalypse was already planned to be in Chapter 3 long before its release. It could also be a reference to Al Niente as it is described as an apocalyptic desolation of the world.
Cyanine is the name of a family of synthetic dyes used for many fluorescent purposes, such as biomedical imaging .
This song is also available in Arcaea, Groove Coaster and OverRapid as part of their respective collaborations.
This song was the longest song in the game for over 3 years, eventually losing the title to crystallized.
Among all songs at the end of a main story chapter, Cyanine's Master chart is the only one that does not possess four simultaneous Rail Notes at any point.

title: Apocalypse
artist: Alice Schach and the Magic Orchestra

title: edge of the world
Trivia: This song's Whisper chart has no Flick notes.

This is the first song that displays characters in its "Before Playing" artwork.

title: Stasis
Trivia: This song has the first Master 16 chart, which was the highest difficulty rating in the game before Immaculate's Master 16+ chart.

This song once held the highest level ratings in all difficulties except for Whisper. Before its release, the highest level for Acoustic, Ultra, and Master were 10, 13, and 15 respectively, and they were for cyanine.
After the intro, the BPM slows down to 90, and then down to just 45 in the start of the bridge.

This is one of six songs to have a 7-level gap between adjacent difficulties (Whisper and Acoustic); the others are Wolves Standing Towards Enemies, Surface,  Bubbles Dream,  Gypsophila, and Astaroth.

This song is available in [https://overrapid.fandom.com/wiki/Stasis OverRapid], WACCA, [https://arcaea.fandom.com/wiki/Stasis Arcaea], [https://phigros.fandom.com/wiki/Stasis Phigros], [https://rotaeno.fandom.com/wiki/Stasis Rotaeno] and Paradigm: Reboot as part of their respective collaborations with Lanota.

title: Tithonus
Trivia: Ena is featured on this song's artwork, holding a Notalium crystal while surrounded by weapons.
* This image is a depiction of the Notalium War.
* Her robe and the weapons are covered in what appears to be blood in this song's 3 challenge unlock artwork, one of the very rare moments blood is shown in the game.
In Greek mythology, Tithonus is an immortal prince that could not die, but would age forever.

title: Weg
Trivia: Weg means "way" or "road" in German.
* According to composer yourmythos, it also refers to Fisica and Ritmo's journey.
This song's artwork features a young Halpas and Ena, the latter weakened from overexposure to Notalium energy.
Once completing three challenges, the Notalium crystals change from blue to purple. This may be a reference to what is to come.
This is the longest song in the Main Story.
The Whisper chart has the highest note count of any level 2 chart.
The Ultra chart has the highest note count of any level 10 chart.
This song was added to WACCA as part of their collaboration with Lanota.

title: Destiny
Trivia: Destiny's artwork depicts Ritmo being approached by the figure of Ena in the Notalium of Life while he is surrounded by vines.
* After completing 3 challenges, various images of Ritmo and Fisica are shown. These are from Side Story 1 and Side Story 2.
This song's Master chart features a memory segment, where a green flick note is shown at different positions, hinting at the order in which the following notes need to be hit.

title: Horizon Blue
artist: Nothing But Requiem feat Aikapin & Chiyoko
Trivia: Horizon Blue and Bloody Marquis have the exact same challenges and difficulties.
The Acoustic chart has the highest note count of any level 9 chart.
The colour of the Notalium within the android may be a reference to Androgynos -1st Phase-.
*Similarly to Androgynos, Horizon Blue has a counterpart, Bloody Marquis.

After playing Destiny and Horizon Blue for the first time, you can't select a "Tune" or "purify" mode until you complete the story (Clear Bloody Marquis and  Wolves Standing Towards Enemies to complete this chapter).
This song is available in Phigros as part of the  Lanota x Phigros collaboration.
This song and an instrumental version can be found on Notebook Record's single "CHAIN & Horizon Blue".
An extended version can be found on Notebook Record's album "Nothing But Requiem Remixes II".

According to the song's composer Halv, the song title is the meaning of Inorganics + Nyx + Prayer.

title: Picasso
Trivia: Picasso is the only Boss song with Master 16 to have an Ultra difficulty lower than 15 (14<sup>+</sup>).
Picasso has the lowest note count out of all Master 16 songs('''1599''').
Before playing this song in Event Challenge, a special animation will play similar to any boss song unlocked in the main chapters.
*Unlike in any main chapter boss song, there is no time limit and the animation can only be replayed via Event Challenge instead of Story Review.

*The animation consists of flying, distorted shots of a stone labyrinth leading to a gate that slowly cracks open before a static effect is played and the screen darkens, before fading into the song's artwork with a kaleidoscope effect applied.
When played via Event Challenge (or Tracklist mode while using the "Gallery Labyrinth" avatar), the following effects are granted:
*Midway through the song, the background will glitch out before returning to normal.

*Just before the chorus, a kaleidoscope effect flashes on the screen before the background is colored in and the Notalium Tuner transforms, now covered in a vibrant, rainbow-colored mosaic until the end of the song.
Along with Aegleseeker, Chronomia and Immaculate, Picasso is one of the few songs to use a unique tuner design.
According to the composer, this song was composed 5 years ago from the data it's introduced to Lanota.
The song title was (possibly) named after [https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pablo_Picasso Pablo Picasso] (1881-1973), a Spanish-French painter.
